When clicking on a confluence link in an email, it is annoying that the {{?src=email}} remains in the browser's address bar. I am constantly copy-and-pasting those urls around (e.g. into hipchat). 1) This leads to non aesthetically pleasing urls everywhere, but 2) it means that any analysis confluence/atlassian are doing on "src=email" is inaccurate.

On page load (in [browsers that support pushstate|http://caniuse.com/#search=pushstate]), Confluence should scrub the url of any {{src=WHATEVER}} query params. If there are no query params left, it should scrub the remaining {{?}}.

